Edinburgh is Scotland's capital and one of the UK's most important business centres. A major financial hub home to Standard Life, Baillie Gifford, and scores of investment firms. A world-renowned festival city that drives a massive tourism economy. A growing tech scene anchored by CodeBase, one of Europe's largest tech incubators. And two universities that consistently rank among the world's best.

That combination creates a fiercely competitive search landscape. I work as an independent SEO consultant for Edinburgh businesses, providing senior-level organic search strategy without the overhead or complexity of working with an agency. You deal directly with me — the person doing the work.

## Why Edinburgh businesses need specialist SEO

Edinburgh's economy is sophisticated and internationally connected. Businesses here are not just competing locally — financial services firms compete nationally and globally, tourism businesses compete with every destination in Europe, and tech companies compete with London, Manchester, and beyond.

This means generic, one-size-fits-all SEO simply does not work. A wealth management firm in Charlotte Square has completely different search dynamics to a restaurant on the Royal Mile, which in turn has nothing in common with a SaaS company in the tech quarter. Each needs a strategy built around its specific audience, competitive set, and commercial goals.

I specialise in building [topical authority](/services/topical-authority/) through semantic SEO. Rather than targeting isolated keywords, I help businesses build comprehensive content architectures that establish them as the definitive resource in their sector. This is the approach that delivers compounding organic growth — the kind that still generates traffic and leads years after the content is published.

## My approach to SEO consulting in Edinburgh

Every engagement starts with a thorough [technical SEO audit](/services/technical-seo-audit/). I examine your site's crawlability, indexation, Core Web Vitals, internal linking structure, structured data, and competitive positioning before making any strategic recommendations. There is no point investing in content or link building on top of a technically compromised site.

From that baseline, my work typically covers:

- **Technical foundations** — Resolving crawl issues, improving site speed, fixing indexation problems, and implementing structured data that helps search engines understand your content properly.
- **Semantic content strategy** — Mapping the full topic landscape for your business, identifying content gaps, and building a publishing roadmap that systematically establishes authority.
- **Competitor analysis** — Understanding exactly who ranks for your target terms, what content they have, and where the gaps in their coverage create opportunities for you.
- **Local visibility** — For businesses serving Edinburgh customers directly, I optimise your Google Business Profile, local citations, and geo-targeted content. My [local SEO](/services/local-seo/) service covers the full spectrum.
- **Ongoing measurement** — I track organic traffic, keyword visibility, conversions, and revenue impact. Every decision is tied to commercial outcomes, not vanity metrics.

## Sectors I work with in Edinburgh

My consulting experience spans the industries that drive Edinburgh's economy:

**Financial services** — Edinburgh is the UK's second-largest financial centre after London. Asset managers, wealth advisers, fintech companies, and insurance firms all operate in a highly regulated sector where trust signals and authoritative content are essential for organic visibility.

**Tourism and hospitality** — The festival city attracts millions of visitors annually, and the competition for tourism-related searches is intense. I help hotels, restaurants, tour operators, and experience providers build organic visibility that reduces dependence on booking platforms and their commissions.

**Education** — The University of Edinburgh, Heriot-Watt, Edinburgh Napier, and Queen Margaret all contribute to a vibrant education ecosystem. I work with educational institutions and edtech businesses to build search visibility for high-value academic and professional queries.

**Legal services** — Edinburgh's legal sector is distinct, operating under Scots law. Law firms here need SEO strategies that account for Scotland-specific legal terminology, jurisdictional differences, and a competitive landscape that includes both local practices and UK-wide firms.

**Tech and SaaS** — Edinburgh's tech scene has grown significantly, with CodeBase, Edinburgh Tech, and university spin-offs driving innovation. Tech companies often have strong products but underinvest in organic search as a growth channel.

**Food and drink** — From Scotch whisky brands to craft breweries and independent restaurants, Edinburgh's food and drink sector has enormous SEO potential, particularly for ecommerce and direct-to-consumer brands.

## How I work with Edinburgh clients

I work remotely with all my clients across the UK, and Edinburgh businesses are no exception. Remote working means you get senior SEO expertise without paying for the overheads of an Edinburgh New Town office. We stay aligned through regular video calls, shared reporting dashboards, and direct communication whenever you need it.

Working with an independent [SEO consultant](/services/seo-consulting/) rather than an agency means there is no account manager filtering your questions or junior staff doing the actual work. Every piece of analysis, every recommendation, and every strategic decision comes directly from me.

For a clear picture of investment levels, visit my [SEO pricing page](/services/how-much-does-seo-cost/). I offer both project-based engagements and monthly retainers, depending on what your business needs.

## Working across Scotland and the UK

While this page focuses on Edinburgh, I also work with businesses across Scotland, including [Glasgow](/services/seo-consultant-glasgow/), as well as clients across the rest of the UK including [London](/services/seo-consultant-london/). If your business operates across multiple regions or internationally, I build strategies that account for that geographic scope.

